reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars OtterBox Commuter Series iPhone 13 Case is AWESOME!
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the OtterBox Commuter Series case for my iPhone 13, and overall, I am quite pleased with its performance and protection. Here's my review of the OtterBox Commuter Series iPhone 13 Case.Design and Build Quality:The design of the Commuter Series case is sleek and stylish. It features a slim profile that doesn't add much bulk to the phone while still providing adequate protection. The case is made of a durable combination of synthetic rubber and polycarbonate, which feels solid and sturdy in hand. The buttons are well-placed and responsive, and the case offers easy access to all ports and features of the iPhone 13.Protection:When it comes to protecting your iPhone 13, the OtterBox Commuter Series case does a commendable job. It offers two layers of protection—a soft inner layer and a hard outer shell—that work together to safeguard the device from drops, bumps, and scratches. The raised edges around the screen and camera provide extra protection against accidental impacts and help prevent any damage to the vulnerable areas.Functionality:The case doesn't hinder the functionality of the iPhone 13 in any significant way. The buttons are easy to press, and the cutouts for the charging port, speakers, and camera are precise, allowing for unobstructed usage. The case also supports wireless charging, which is a convenient feature to have.Grip and Handling:The OtterBox Commuter Series case offers a good grip, thanks to the textured back and the slightly raised edges. It feels secure in hand, minimizing the chances of accidental slips and drops. However, the smooth sides of the case can sometimes make it feel a bit slippery, especially if your hands are sweaty or oily.Drawbacks:While the case does a great job in terms of protection and functionality, it's worth noting that it might not be the most stylish option available. It lacks some of the aesthetic flair that other cases offer, and the color options are relatively limited. Additionally, the case is not completely dustproof or waterproof, so it may not be the best choice for those who require extreme protection against environmental elements.Conclusion:In conclusion, the OtterBox Commuter Series iPhone 13 Case is a reliable and sturdy choice for anyone looking to protect their device from everyday wear and tear. It provides solid protection, maintains the phone's functionality, and offers a good grip. While it may lack some aesthetic appeal and isn't completely dustproof or waterproof, it remains a practical option for those seeking a durable and functional case for their iPhone 13.Overall, I would highly recommend the OtterBox Commuter Series case to iPhone 13 owners who prioritize protection and functionality over flashy designs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Protects my phone well
reviews.reviewText: It’s a light weight case, easy to install and of good quality. It is also comfortable in my hands. A bit of dirt will make its way in between the case but I clean it up routinely to prevent scratches. The rubber plug that sits in the charging port was exactly what I was looking for so I wouldn’t have to worry about gunk building up in there. Otter box quality is there for sure. It has survived drops on concrete, pavement, dirt, and steel which hitting the bucket of a skid steer or bed of a dump truck. It is the commuter model so the fact that it has protected my phone from heavy use makes this a good buy.
